AN ACT relating to transportation; requiring the Department of
Transportation to report certain information on the
progress and need for certain transportation projects
relating to wildlife; revising the qualifications for a
Deputy Director of the Department; revising provisions
relating to the proposal for certain highway projects the
Department must submit to the Board of Directors of the
Department; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Department of Transportation to develop an inventory
2 of connectivity needs on the state highway system where the implementation of
3 wildlife crossings and other related highway features will support certain purposes
4 relating to wildlife. (NRS 408.661) Existing law also requires: (1) the Board of
5 Directors of the Department to adopt a plan for measuring the performance of the
6 Department; and (2) the Director of the Department to prepare a report, based upon
7 certain performance measurements, on the level of achievement of each division of
8 the Department and the Department as a whole which must include, among other
9 requirements, the scheduling, scope, cost and progress of any current or proposed
10 highway projects. (NRS 408.133) Section 1 of this bill requires that the information
11 in the report prepared by the Director relating to current and proposed highway
12 projects include the progress of any current or proposed project identified in the
13 inventory of connectivity and the need for such a project.
14 Existing law requires each Deputy Director of the Department to: (1) hold a
15 master’s degree in public or business administration, or meet certain other
16 educational requirements; and (2) have at least 15 years of progressively
17 responsible experience in engineering or project management, or meet certain other
18 experiential requirements. (NRS 408.178) Section 1.1 of this bill instead requires
19 each Deputy Director to: (1) hold a bachelor’s degree in business, economics or
