24 Existing law further requires the Department to prepare a written analysis of the
25 costs and benefits of each proposal for a highway project that will cost $25 million
26 or more. (NRS 408.3195) Section 1.3 of this bill instead requires that the
27 Department prepare such an analysis of each proposal for a highway project that
28 will cost $50 million or more. Section 1.3 additionally requires the Department to
29 include in the analysis for a highway project proposal a discussion of the number of
30 wildlife-vehicle collisions in the highway district and the value of any mitigation of
31 wildlife-vehicle collisions from the design, construction and use of wildlife
32 crossings.
